We want to add support for the new **JWT authentication** in sensenet. 

### Requirements

- authentication is server-specific, not a global setting
- **no breaking change**, the previous login api and auth workflow should still work (basic or NTLM auth)
- hide _token refresh_ mechanism from callers (client developers), that should be done automatically by the client library internally
- the client library does **not** save/serialize token data and cookies, only handles in-memory info
- the caller should be able to **get and set** all auth data in a **serializable** format (so that users do not have to give their un/pw every time they start the client app)

### Public API proposal
```csharp
var server = new ServerContext { Url = "https://example.com" };

// new method: authentication
await server.LoginAsync("admin", "admin");

ClientContext.Initialize(new[] { server });

// do stuff (using the globally defined server)
await Content.LoadAsync(123);

// do stuff (explicitely defined server)
await Content.ExistsAsync("/Root/folder1", server);

// new method: optional in-memory logout?
server.Logout();
```

### Internal API proposal
#### Extend the server context class
```csharp
public class ServerContext
{
    public IAuthenticationProvider AuthenticationProvider { get; set; }

    public async Task LoginAsync(string username, string password)
    {
        // preparation...
        // ...
    
        await AuthenticationProvider.LoginAsync(this);
    
        // do stuff with the response...
    }
}
``` 
#### Auth provider interface
```csharp
public interface IAuthenticationProvider
{
    Task LoginAsync(ServerContext server);
    void SetAuthentication(ServerContext server, WebRequest request);
}
``` 
#### Jwt implementation
```csharp
public class JwtAuthenticationProvider : IAuthenticationProvider
{
   // interface implementation
}
```

